Two pilots died after a Chinese Navy fighter jet crashed during training on Tuesday, the Defence Ministry said in a statement. The jet crashed in Ledong Li Autonomous County, on the southern island of Hainan, according to the statement. An investigation into the cause of the crash was underway. (dpa/NAN) How NAF pilot died  in Abuja jet crash Air Force jet crashes in Yola, kills pilot Pakistani female fighter pilot dies in crash